OL,3,CCash spending limits for Guernsey's
OL,4,Ccommittees to combat #2 million deficit
OL,6,FTo cope with this overspend, all
OL,7,FCommittees have been given cash limits
OL,8,Fahead of next year's Budget, adding
OL,9,Fthat "no one is getting everything
OL,10,Fthey asked for".
OL,12,FDeputy St Pier explained that one of
OL,13,Fthe areas of expenditure which has
OL,14,Fcreated "risk" in 2025 is financial
OL,15,Fchallenges relating to staffing
OL,16,Fdifficulties in the Committee for
OL,17,FHealth & Social Care.
OL,19,FThis has resulted in a forecast
OL,20,Foverspend of #2.8 million in that
OL,21,Fdepartment.
