OL,3,CCash spending limits for Guernsey's
OL,4,Ccommittees to combat #2 million deficit
OL,6,FWhilst Deputy St Pier conceded the #2
OL,7,Fmillion deficit is "certainly an
OL,8,Fimprovement on the budgeted position",
OL,9,Fthe States continues to "spend more
OL,10,Fthan we generate on a day-to-day
OL,11,Fbasis", adding this is "a challenging
OL,12,Fstarting point to putting together a
OL,13,Fbudget for 2026".
OL,15,FThe island's financial position should
OL,16,Fimprove when revenues from large
OL,17,Fmultinational companies based in the
OL,18,FChannel Islands are brought in as a
OL,19,Fresult of the introduction of the
OL,20,F'pillar two' tax scheme.
